Rulemaking Analyses and Notices 


The Administrative Procedure Act (APA), 5 U.S.C. 551 

et seq., 

allows agencies engaged in rulemaking to dispense with prior notice and opportunity for comment when the agency for
good cause finds that such procedures are impracticable, unnecessary, or are contrary to the public interest. 5 U.S.C.
553(b)(3)(B). As previously discussed, on December 21, 1990 (55 FR 52402), the RSPA comprehensively revised the
regulatory requirements of the HMR with respect to hazard communication, classification, and packaging requirements.
The revisions adopted the United Nations' Recommendations on the Transportation of Dangerous Goods, and were intended
to further international regulatory uniformity. This FHWA final rule changes terminology and descriptions used
in the FMCSR to reflect the changes made by the RSPA to the HMR. These amendments are technical in nature, and do not alter
