<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY: 

The Commission is exempting from regulation the transportation by rail of grease or inedible tallow, etc. (STCC No.
20-143). These commodities are added to the list of exempt commodities in 49 CFR part 1039, as set forth below.
This exemption does not embrace exemptions from regulation of car hire and car service. 



On October 21, 1993, at 58 FR 54320, we requested comments on a proposal by the Association of American Railroads (AAR)
to exempt from regulation the railroad transportation of grease or inedible tallow. The comments have been received
and analyzed. We are approving AAR's proposal. 


 

</SUMMARY>
